WEBVTT

00:11.302 --> 00:13.805
[Pat on radio] <i>Tell me you're not</i>
<i>still talking to the farmer.</i>

00:13.888 --> 00:15.807
[Mark] <i>Are you eavesdropping</i>
<i>on my conversation?</i>

00:15.890 --> 00:16.975
[chuckles]

00:18.059 --> 00:19.769
Uh, your girl just waved at me.

00:19.853 --> 00:20.687
-Hi.
-Hi.

00:20.770 --> 00:23.523
For once, that doesn't threaten me,
married man.

00:24.190 --> 00:25.191
Okay.

00:29.821 --> 00:31.072
[woman] Whoa!

00:31.614 --> 00:33.408
[distant whooshing]

00:37.829 --> 00:39.831
[gasping]

00:41.207 --> 00:42.167
Wow.

00:42.250 --> 00:45.712
Pat. Pat, get your lame ass up here,
'cause... 'cause it's happening.

00:45.795 --> 00:46.963
[Pat chuckles]

00:47.547 --> 00:48.506
[computer beeps]

00:48.590 --> 00:50.425
[alarm sounds]

00:53.511 --> 00:54.512
Hey, uh...

00:55.263 --> 00:57.724
are you experiencing
a fluctuation in temperature out there?

00:57.807 --> 00:59.851
Yeah, I can feel your girl getting cold

00:59.934 --> 01:02.103
because you're hiding out
in a heated yurt.

01:02.187 --> 01:04.105
No, Mark, there's...
there's something, uh...

01:04.189 --> 01:05.607
[loud whooshing]

01:05.690 --> 01:07.400
-[man 1] Whoa!
-[crowd gasping]

01:07.484 --> 01:08.651
-[explosion]
-[woman] Whoa!

01:08.735 --> 01:09.778
[man 2] Oh, man!

01:12.405 --> 01:13.740
Oh!

01:13.823 --> 01:15.116
-[computers beeping]
-Mark?

01:15.200 --> 01:17.452
[crowd chattering excitedly]

01:18.244 --> 01:20.163
Oh, my...

01:20.246 --> 01:22.665
[computers beeping]

01:22.999 --> 01:24.834
-Mark?
-[Mark] <i>Pat, can you see--</i>

01:24.918 --> 01:27.879
The radiation level's off the charts.
Are you okay?

01:27.962 --> 01:29.130
[static over radio]

01:29.214 --> 01:30.673
[whooshing]

01:31.549 --> 01:32.634
[static]

01:33.176 --> 01:34.010
[Mark] <i>Pat?</i>

01:34.094 --> 01:34.928
Mark.

01:35.470 --> 01:37.472
[distant explosion]

01:38.932 --> 01:40.100
Okay, okay.

01:40.391 --> 01:41.559
Um, uh...

01:51.069 --> 01:51.903
Mark?

02:02.622 --> 02:04.624
[projectiles whooshing]

02:07.502 --> 02:09.170
-[sizzling]
-Ow!

02:09.254 --> 02:10.088
What the hell?

02:11.548 --> 02:13.174
-Mark, can you hear me? Ow!
-[sizzling]

02:13.716 --> 02:15.552
Are you in the middle of this stuff?

02:15.635 --> 02:17.178
-Oh!
-[sizzling]

02:18.847 --> 02:19.681
Mark!

02:21.724 --> 02:23.226
[banging]

02:23.309 --> 02:25.186
-[computers beeping]
-[alarm sounds]

02:41.411 --> 02:43.746
[voices whispering indistinctly]

02:45.039 --> 02:46.541
["Dear Love" by Rachel Ann Weiss plays]

02:46.624 --> 02:48.626
<i>♪ And all the roses seem to fade ♪</i>

02:48.877 --> 02:51.421
<i>♪ And somehow, I have lost my way ♪</i>

02:51.504 --> 02:54.174
[Pat] Okay, let's see here.
These are the choices.

02:54.257 --> 02:56.426
Okay, there is an <i>X-Men</i> movie,

02:56.509 --> 03:00.054
uh, a <i>Godzilla</i> remake,
and a <i>Planet of the Apes </i>sequel.

03:01.097 --> 03:02.515
Uh, I can't do a movie.

03:04.142 --> 03:05.935
Yeah, we can do something else.

03:06.019 --> 03:07.729
Um, we could go for a hike.

03:08.188 --> 03:09.314
Um...

03:10.398 --> 03:12.358
There's a music festival in Piedmont Park.

03:12.901 --> 03:15.403
I don't care.
I'm just so glad you're finally here.

03:17.530 --> 03:18.448
Pat, we need to talk.

03:19.240 --> 03:20.074
About?

03:21.492 --> 03:22.452
This isn't working.

03:25.330 --> 03:26.414
I agree.

03:27.624 --> 03:31.044
Which is why I think you should move here.

03:31.711 --> 03:32.587
No, I...

03:33.421 --> 03:34.923
I'm dealing with some personal stuff.

03:35.006 --> 03:36.758
Since Iceland,
I've been having some problems.

03:36.841 --> 03:37.926
Hey, hey.

03:38.760 --> 03:41.554
That... That's just the distance talking.

03:41.971 --> 03:45.058
You know, you'll feel differently
when you're living here.

03:46.809 --> 03:47.894
I know how I feel.

03:49.354 --> 03:52.273
Yeah, but I'm--
I'm saying that will change.

03:53.107 --> 03:55.818
-You're not listening.
-Well, you're not making sense.

03:55.902 --> 03:57.487
Actually, I'm being very clear.

03:57.570 --> 04:00.073
Well, you're not... you're not being fair.

04:00.156 --> 04:01.741
You know, I do everything for us.

04:01.824 --> 04:04.369
-I travel to see you all the time.
-[laughs]

04:04.452 --> 04:07.080
I plan our time together,
I pay for everything...

04:07.163 --> 04:08.623
See, this is the problem.

04:08.706 --> 04:10.416
You know, you come on so strong.

04:11.167 --> 04:14.671
Flowers, and trips, and remembering
my mother's birthday, for God's sake.

04:14.754 --> 04:15.922
-How is that--
-But when things

04:16.005 --> 04:18.216
aren't exactly the way you want,
you go nuts.

04:18.299 --> 04:20.927
-You're trying to break up with me.
-I'm not trying.

04:22.637 --> 04:23.471
I'm doing it.

04:25.556 --> 04:26.557
Where are you going?

04:26.641 --> 04:28.476
I'm staying with Jill, at her cabin.

04:28.893 --> 04:31.646
You... you already planned that?
Hey, hey, hey. We need to talk about--

04:31.729 --> 04:33.022
-Let go of me, please.
-[sizzling]

04:33.106 --> 04:35.566
-No, no, this isn't just your decision.
-Let go of me!

04:36.734 --> 04:37.986
Oh! What the hell?

04:38.319 --> 04:39.654
Ah, why did you do that?

04:39.737 --> 04:42.073
[Kerry] I told you
I was dealing with some stuff.

04:42.156 --> 04:43.783
-Well, so am I.
-[electricity crackles]

04:43.866 --> 04:44.951
-Pat?
-[exhales]

04:45.034 --> 04:46.494
[electricity crackling]

04:47.662 --> 04:48.538
What's happening?

04:49.580 --> 04:51.291
I can't make it stop.

04:53.251 --> 04:54.210
[Kerry] Oh, my God, Pat.

04:55.044 --> 04:56.462
[thunder rumbling]

04:56.629 --> 04:57.630
Pat, what's--

04:57.714 --> 04:59.048
What's happening, Pat?

04:59.132 --> 04:59.966
Pat!

05:00.049 --> 05:01.259
Pat, stop!

05:02.135 --> 05:03.261
No.

05:03.761 --> 05:04.595
Please, Pat!

05:04.929 --> 05:06.139
[Kerry screams]

05:06.389 --> 05:07.390
No, Pat!

05:10.977 --> 05:12.228
[groaning]

05:12.312 --> 05:13.521
[gasps]

05:15.023 --> 05:15.898
[thundering]

05:18.651 --> 05:19.610
[screams]

05:20.403 --> 05:22.405
[screams]

05:25.158 --> 05:26.367
[sobbing]

05:29.787 --> 05:31.748
[thundering]

05:40.256 --> 05:42.425
Hi, Esperanza. It's me, Dion.

05:42.717 --> 05:45.261
Well, actually, you already know that
because you're looking at me,

05:45.345 --> 05:47.096
so I should probably edit that out.

05:47.180 --> 05:48.931
-Dion!
-[Dion] So, hey.

05:49.015 --> 05:50.892
-Hey, are you okay?
-You're home!

05:50.975 --> 05:53.478
All right, we need to go.
We need to go right now.

05:53.561 --> 05:56.022
-Why? And why is it so dark outside?
-Hey, no.

05:56.105 --> 05:58.983
We need to get in the car,
and we need to get out of here right now.

05:59.067 --> 06:00.026
-But--
-[Nicole] No buts.

06:00.109 --> 06:01.652
Not now, okay? Let's go.

06:01.736 --> 06:03.196
-Can't we--
-Dion.

06:03.571 --> 06:05.698
It's the Crooked Man. Okay?

06:05.782 --> 06:06.741
[panting]

06:06.824 --> 06:08.576
Come on, come on. Grab your stuff.

06:08.659 --> 06:10.953
-We gotta go, Pinchy!
-Hurry, okay?

06:12.038 --> 06:12.914
Hurry!

06:28.638 --> 06:30.515
[birds chirping]

06:32.266 --> 06:33.893
[number pad beeping]

06:38.815 --> 06:39.649
Dion?

06:42.527 --> 06:43.361
Nicole?

06:49.450 --> 06:50.284
Nicole?

06:50.910 --> 06:52.829
[dialing]

06:55.998 --> 06:58.084
[cell phone ringing]

06:59.502 --> 07:01.629
[cell phone continues ringing]

07:02.463 --> 07:03.714
[Dion] Who's that?

07:04.674 --> 07:07.427
You know what? It doesn't matter.
I'll call him back later.

07:08.052 --> 07:11.347
Can I use your phone?
I have to call Esperanza.

07:11.431 --> 07:14.392
-Not now.
-I have to. She's so mad at me.

07:14.475 --> 07:15.810
[inhales deeply, exhales]

07:15.893 --> 07:18.521
We can just talk about it
when we get there, okay?

07:19.105 --> 07:20.857
Get where? Where are we going?

07:22.275 --> 07:23.317
Where it's safe.

07:25.194 --> 07:29.031
<i>♪ I should be ashamed</i>
<i>How I pray for it ♪</i>

07:30.116 --> 07:33.536
<i>♪ When you're not around</i>
<i>I just ache for it ♪</i>

07:33.619 --> 07:36.289
<i>♪ Sit around and wait for it ♪</i>

07:37.165 --> 07:38.291
[banging]

07:39.834 --> 07:42.920
<i>♪ It should never feel this good ♪</i>

07:43.004 --> 07:43.963
[banging]

07:46.090 --> 07:47.216
-Oh.
-What are...

07:47.300 --> 07:48.509
-Hey.
-What are you doing here?

07:48.593 --> 07:51.220
Um, I tried calling the hospital,
but they said you weren't there.

07:51.304 --> 07:52.847
They didn't know
when you would be, so...

07:52.930 --> 07:55.057
Yeah, I'm... I'm on an indefinite leave.

07:55.141 --> 07:57.435
Unofficially fired,
waiting to get officially fired.

07:57.518 --> 07:59.353
Yeah. Um, where's Nicole?

08:00.229 --> 08:02.273
-Uh...
-What is up with you right now?

08:02.356 --> 08:03.483
I'm, uh...

08:04.400 --> 08:06.277
I'm just...
I'm just worried about your sister.

08:06.360 --> 08:08.362
She's not returning my texts, and I...

08:09.197 --> 08:10.364
[inhales deeply, exhales]

08:10.448 --> 08:13.284
I'm afraid she's gonna hurt Dion.

08:13.826 --> 08:15.745
Hurt Dion? In what world?

08:16.204 --> 08:17.705
She's not in her right mind, Kat.

08:17.788 --> 08:20.666
Like, I don't... I don't know
if she's having a breakdown or what,

08:20.750 --> 08:23.878
but she's... she's off the rails,
and I really need to find her.

08:23.961 --> 08:25.838
Okay, she was fine
the last time I talked to her.

08:25.922 --> 08:28.090
-Well, when was that? Because--
-[cell phone rings]

08:29.759 --> 08:31.677
Who is it? Is that Nicole?

08:32.887 --> 08:34.388
-Mind your business.
-Was that Nicole?

08:34.472 --> 08:36.807
-As a matter of fact, I need you to leave.
-Well...

08:36.891 --> 08:39.519
No, I'm not having a good day.
I don't feel like doing this with you.

08:39.602 --> 08:41.103
Can you just talk to me for one second?

08:41.187 --> 08:43.105
-No, I wanna go back to sleep.
-Kat, can I just...

08:44.440 --> 08:47.151
Sorry, I don't...
I don't mean to scare you, but I'm...

08:49.237 --> 08:50.613
I am really concerned.

08:51.030 --> 08:53.449
I need to know that Dion is okay.

08:53.991 --> 08:57.286
So if you could just put my mind at ease
and get her on the phone,

08:57.370 --> 08:58.996
or tell me where she took him...

08:59.455 --> 09:02.291
otherwise, I think--
I have to call the cops.

09:04.043 --> 09:05.545
She took him to see our folks.

09:06.003 --> 09:07.797
-In St. Louis?
-Yeah, just for a few days.

09:07.880 --> 09:09.006
She said she needed a break.

09:09.715 --> 09:11.592
But you don't have to worry.

09:12.593 --> 09:14.971
Nicole would never let
anything happen to Dion.

09:15.805 --> 09:17.431
She would protect that kid with her life.

09:23.229 --> 09:24.063
[locks door]

09:30.611 --> 09:32.113
[cell phone ringing]

09:33.030 --> 09:34.949
-Oh, Kat.
-[Kat] <i>Where are you?</i>

09:36.325 --> 09:38.828
[sighs] I was on my way to you,
but you didn't answer your phone.

09:38.911 --> 09:41.330
Pat was here acting like a freak
looking for you.

09:41.664 --> 09:43.165
-Are you okay?
-[Nicole] <i>No.</i>

09:43.249 --> 09:46.669
<i>The storm that killed Mark,</i>
<i>it's not just a storm.</i>

09:46.752 --> 09:49.213
Dion calls it the Crooked Man. It--

09:50.214 --> 09:53.759
-It came to our house again today.
-[Kat] <i>Again? What are you talking about?</i>

09:53.843 --> 09:55.177
Why didn't you call somebody?

09:55.261 --> 09:57.305
It's a supernatural storm, Kat.

09:57.388 --> 09:59.307
[Kat] <i>But there must be something</i>
<i>we can do.</i>

09:59.390 --> 10:01.142
Just come here, and we'll figure it out.

10:01.225 --> 10:03.769
No. No, we have to get away.
We have to hide.

10:03.853 --> 10:06.230
Whoa, Nic, what are you talking about?
Hide where?

10:06.314 --> 10:08.024
[Nicole] <i>It's better if I don't tell you.</i>

10:08.107 --> 10:10.151
I don't want this thing
coming after you, too.

10:10.234 --> 10:11.319
-Niki.
-[Nicole] <i>I gotta go.</i>

10:11.402 --> 10:12.945
-[Kat] <i>No, wait, Niki. Wait.</i>
-I love you.

10:13.029 --> 10:13.946
[disconnects call]

10:24.749 --> 10:26.083
[deep breath]

10:26.167 --> 10:27.001
[exhales]

10:27.918 --> 10:28.878
[message transmits]

10:28.961 --> 10:30.254
[sniffs, exhales]

10:31.797 --> 10:33.424
[inhales, exhales]

10:38.137 --> 10:38.971
Mmm...

10:43.517 --> 10:44.769
-[dialing]
-[exhales]

10:44.852 --> 10:45.895
[line ringing]

10:47.897 --> 10:48.731
[exhales]

10:49.649 --> 10:51.317
-[Nicole] <i>You know what to do.</i>
-[beep]

10:51.400 --> 10:53.361
Hi, Nicole. Um, it's me.

10:53.444 --> 10:54.403
[chuckles nervously]

10:55.237 --> 10:57.198
So, I... I...

10:57.573 --> 11:00.034
I know I made a mistake.
I was a little out of line.

11:00.117 --> 11:01.494
I, um...

11:01.577 --> 11:03.704
I'm really sorry, okay?

11:03.788 --> 11:05.623
But, you know, you can't just...

11:05.706 --> 11:06.540
[inhales]

11:06.624 --> 11:10.503
blow up everything that we have
because of one silly mistake.

11:10.753 --> 11:11.629
It's not fair.

11:11.879 --> 11:14.840
Uh, it's not fair to me or to Dion, and...

11:18.469 --> 11:19.303
[disconnects call]

11:31.357 --> 11:32.316
[message transmits]

11:36.362 --> 11:38.656
[birds squawking and chirping]

11:55.381 --> 11:56.674
[hammering]

11:59.552 --> 12:03.097
[Dion] Oh, man. Boards on my window?
It's like I'm in jail.

12:05.141 --> 12:06.726
[hammering]

12:10.604 --> 12:12.606
-[hammering continues]
-[sighs]

12:17.069 --> 12:18.487
-[hammering]
-[exhales]

12:25.494 --> 12:27.163
[hammering continues]

12:27.538 --> 12:28.622
[notification chimes]

12:43.429 --> 12:44.305
[phone chimes]

12:46.557 --> 12:47.391
[exhales]

12:47.475 --> 12:50.770
[breathing heavily]

12:50.853 --> 12:52.104
[drill whirring]

12:54.982 --> 12:56.192
We have to go home.

12:58.402 --> 13:00.821
I'm sorry, honey, but you can't.

13:01.739 --> 13:04.658
Esperanza won't answer my texts.
She'll be there.

13:05.034 --> 13:07.578
-I can say "I'm sorry" in person.
-No, honey.

13:07.661 --> 13:08.954
[whirring]

13:09.872 --> 13:11.040
And I wanna talk to Pat.

13:11.123 --> 13:11.957
[whirring]

13:12.583 --> 13:14.376
Pat and I had a disagreement.

13:14.794 --> 13:15.753
About what?

13:16.378 --> 13:17.213
Um...

13:18.756 --> 13:21.050
Do you know what boundaries are?

13:21.634 --> 13:23.177
Like in dodgeball?

13:23.594 --> 13:24.428
Sort of.

13:25.429 --> 13:28.432
Um, but people
have all kinds of boundaries,

13:29.058 --> 13:31.227
and when someone doesn't want something,

13:31.936 --> 13:32.978
you have to listen.

13:33.312 --> 13:36.357
Okay? It's called
respecting people's boundaries.

13:36.607 --> 13:37.775
What did Pat do wrong?

13:39.401 --> 13:42.738
He wanted a different kind
of relationship with me than I wanted.

13:43.239 --> 13:45.407
Ugh, like a kissing kind of relationship?

13:45.491 --> 13:46.909
-Ugh!
-[Nicole chuckles]

13:46.992 --> 13:48.035
The point is...

13:48.369 --> 13:49.453
is that I said no.

13:50.579 --> 13:51.622
And he didn't listen.

13:51.705 --> 13:54.750
He thought he knew
what was better for me than I did.

13:59.755 --> 14:00.589
What's wrong?

14:01.006 --> 14:04.301
I think I didn't respect
Esperanza's boundaries.

14:05.886 --> 14:07.054
Okay, what happened?

14:07.137 --> 14:09.682
I lifted her up out of her chair
with magic.

14:10.683 --> 14:11.517
Why?

14:11.600 --> 14:14.103
I thought she'd like it,
but she got really angry.

14:15.813 --> 14:20.025
[sighs] Well, did she ever talk
about wanting to come out of her chair?

14:20.609 --> 14:24.697
No, but Jonathan is good at drawing,
like she is,

14:24.780 --> 14:26.407
and they play Zelda,

14:26.490 --> 14:28.033
but she was my friend first.

14:28.117 --> 14:29.952
Oh, Bug.

14:30.494 --> 14:31.954
I'm going home.

14:32.037 --> 14:33.205
No, we can't.

14:33.289 --> 14:34.623
I'm going home!

14:35.416 --> 14:37.710
Dion! I didn't know
you could still do that.

14:37.793 --> 14:38.669
Me neither!

14:41.463 --> 14:42.423
Stop.

14:42.506 --> 14:45.426
I'm not gonna let my friends down,
or Jonathan.

14:45.509 --> 14:47.136
Abracadabra!

14:47.219 --> 14:48.178
Do not teleport.

14:49.972 --> 14:51.390
[Dion] Ugh, not my room.

14:51.932 --> 14:53.017
Di...

14:53.100 --> 14:54.852
Bug, you're going the wrong way.

14:57.313 --> 14:58.230
[door opens]

15:08.949 --> 15:11.160
I think Pinchy's
a little worried about you.

15:13.454 --> 15:14.496
Charlotte lied.

15:16.165 --> 15:17.082
About what?

15:18.626 --> 15:21.712
She said I'd be able to teleport
if I really needed to.

15:22.379 --> 15:23.422
You just did.

15:25.090 --> 15:26.592
Not to where I want to go.

15:28.093 --> 15:33.098
You will make things right with Esperanza
as soon as you get back.

15:34.767 --> 15:35.851
I promise.

15:41.523 --> 15:43.025
[wind howling]

15:43.108 --> 15:44.944
[shutters clattering]

15:55.162 --> 15:56.246
I'll be right back.

16:09.051 --> 16:10.386
[wind howling]

16:32.533 --> 16:33.367
[message chimes]

16:49.633 --> 16:51.051
[dramatic music plays]

17:02.146 --> 17:03.522
[wind subsides]

17:03.605 --> 17:04.648
[birds chirping]

17:07.192 --> 17:08.027
Uh...

17:18.120 --> 17:19.163
-Hey.
-[gasps]

17:20.164 --> 17:21.123
Are you guys okay?

17:22.458 --> 17:24.376
What did-- What are you doing here?

17:24.460 --> 17:27.838
Uh, Dion, asked me to come. See?

17:28.714 --> 17:30.215
But the storm. Did you--

17:30.966 --> 17:32.301
You didn't drive here.
I didn't see your car.

17:32.426 --> 17:33.552
[stammers] How did you get here?

17:33.635 --> 17:36.764
Did you board these windows yourself?
Because that's a-- That was a good job.

17:36.847 --> 17:39.308
-It must have taken you all night. Dion!
-Hey, stay right there.

17:39.391 --> 17:40.225
Ah!

17:41.226 --> 17:42.352
[exhales]

17:43.187 --> 17:45.689
Those are the same things
that were on the fox.

17:45.773 --> 17:49.026
-Are you sick? Is that why you're here?
-No, no, no, no, no. Um...

17:49.234 --> 17:51.737
I'm here because you weren't
answering my calls,

17:51.820 --> 17:52.696
or my texts.

17:52.780 --> 17:53.614
You...

17:54.031 --> 17:54.990
you cut me out.

17:56.075 --> 17:57.076
Get out of my house.

17:57.159 --> 17:58.577
No, I need to talk to Dion.

17:58.994 --> 18:00.579
-Dion!
-Hey, I said no.

18:00.996 --> 18:01.830
[yelps]

18:02.581 --> 18:03.415
Dion!

18:03.999 --> 18:05.167
No. Dion.

18:07.252 --> 18:08.337
[pants]

18:08.420 --> 18:09.254
[gasps]

18:09.671 --> 18:10.506
[pants]

18:12.549 --> 18:13.467
[chuckles]

18:14.384 --> 18:15.219
Yes!

18:18.931 --> 18:19.973
Buddy!

18:20.432 --> 18:22.059
Whoa, you must be tired.

18:29.233 --> 18:30.442
Dion, where are you?

18:31.318 --> 18:32.945
[coughing]

18:33.570 --> 18:34.404
[Nicole] Dion!

18:35.823 --> 18:37.491
He did it. Wow.

18:38.242 --> 18:39.284
That is amazing.

18:40.244 --> 18:43.372
You think that Dion can heal you
like he healed that fox?

18:43.455 --> 18:46.583
That's why he was in the hospital.
You made him try to heal you!

18:46.667 --> 18:49.336
[yells] Hey! I didn't do anything.

18:49.419 --> 18:51.505
He wanted to help me because he loves me.

18:52.381 --> 18:53.257
And I love him.

18:54.216 --> 18:56.510
And I love you.

18:58.137 --> 19:00.973
But you had to go and screw
that whole thing up for everybody.

19:02.182 --> 19:04.768
But you're not gonna hurt him, are you?

19:04.852 --> 19:05.686
Nicole.

19:06.854 --> 19:09.690
Do you... do you have any idea

19:10.149 --> 19:11.567
how much pain I am in?

19:12.901 --> 19:14.570
How close I've been to dying?

19:14.653 --> 19:17.739
The thing that gave everybody else powers
is eating me alive.

19:17.823 --> 19:20.200
And then Dion comes along
and he can fix it all.

19:20.284 --> 19:21.410
But it would kill him.

19:21.493 --> 19:22.536
Which is...

19:23.328 --> 19:25.247
why I never asked him to heal me.

19:25.330 --> 19:27.040
Okay? I wanted us to be a family.

19:28.417 --> 19:31.003
I-I-I would have gone on
absorbing other powered people.

19:31.086 --> 19:32.838
-Oh, no. God.
-Until I ran out of them.

19:32.921 --> 19:33.755
You...

19:34.298 --> 19:35.132
killed Mark.

19:35.215 --> 19:36.049
Oh, my God.

19:36.633 --> 19:39.303
He should have told me
he was going to New Orleans!

19:39.386 --> 19:42.055
Suddenly, he was there,
and I couldn't stop.

19:42.139 --> 19:43.223
[groans]

19:43.307 --> 19:44.600
-Hey.
-I couldn't stop.

19:44.683 --> 19:46.476
-Just-- Let's, um...
-Oh, God.

19:46.560 --> 19:48.770
What do you want?
I mean, how do we... how do we fix this?

19:49.188 --> 19:50.647
-No.
-There's a way to do it.

19:50.731 --> 19:51.648
-No, no, no.
-There--

19:51.732 --> 19:53.233
No, no, no, no. You made your choice.

19:53.317 --> 19:56.195
And so now I'm gonna do
what I need to do to survive.

19:59.406 --> 20:01.658
-You can't have him!
-[groans]

20:03.035 --> 20:03.952
[Nicole whimpers]

20:04.870 --> 20:06.246
[Pat scoffs]

20:06.330 --> 20:07.956
You really don't get it, do you?

20:08.749 --> 20:11.210
[electricity crackles]

20:13.629 --> 20:15.380
[panicked breathing]

20:29.478 --> 20:31.480
[fire crackling]

21:21.363 --> 21:22.239
[Brett] Hmm.

21:24.700 --> 21:25.617
I'm reporting you.

21:27.327 --> 21:28.662
Do what you've gotta do, man.

21:28.745 --> 21:30.247
I have early classes.

21:31.081 --> 21:33.250
[sighs] Then you'd best get to bed.

21:34.167 --> 21:35.252
You've been drinking?

21:35.585 --> 21:37.504
-Come from a party?
-[inhales]

21:37.587 --> 21:38.588
[sighs]

21:38.672 --> 21:40.048
Get out of my face, Brett.

21:40.132 --> 21:43.760
It's none of your business what I did
before I came to work,

21:44.177 --> 21:46.179
-what I do after work...
-[man shushing]

22:04.614 --> 22:06.116
You have too many books out.

22:09.077 --> 22:10.037
I'm sorry, what?

22:10.537 --> 22:12.039
The maximum is four.

22:12.581 --> 22:13.582
And you have...

22:14.333 --> 22:16.126
-Six.
-Six.

22:16.543 --> 22:18.378
[scoffs] Yeah, but nobody's in here.

22:18.754 --> 22:20.630
Rules are rules. I enforce the rules.

22:21.423 --> 22:22.257
[Mark] Hm.

22:22.674 --> 22:23.592
How was the party?

22:24.801 --> 22:26.845
-Hmm?
-That is why you're late, right?

22:26.928 --> 22:28.388
How do you know that I'm late?

22:28.472 --> 22:31.391
Because your shift starts at 1:00.
It's a little past 3:00.

22:32.100 --> 22:34.770
I'm here a lot. You're late a lot.

22:36.563 --> 22:39.024
-[scoffs] What, are you stalking me or...?
-No, ma'am.

22:39.107 --> 22:42.110
I'm stalking education and knowledge.

22:44.863 --> 22:46.698
Hmm. I need coffee.

22:47.282 --> 22:49.284
I like mine with two sugars. Thank you.

22:52.746 --> 22:53.872
I'm not a waitress.

22:55.791 --> 22:58.543
Except at my other job,
where I'm a waitress.

22:59.669 --> 23:01.380
That's a lot of jobs. Why so many?

23:03.298 --> 23:05.675
Maybe my dad didn't want to pay
for a dance major.

23:05.759 --> 23:07.469
Mmm. I see, I see.

23:07.761 --> 23:10.055
Well, I mean, we can get him on the phone.
I'll talk to him.

23:10.138 --> 23:12.224
[laughs] And what would you say to him?

23:12.307 --> 23:13.350
Shh...

23:13.683 --> 23:15.227
Stop shushing me.

23:15.310 --> 23:16.686
Okay, well, come down here.

23:17.646 --> 23:18.480
Come on.

23:20.357 --> 23:22.484
Okay, smart-ass,
what would you say to him?

23:23.985 --> 23:26.530
I mean, I'd tell him that art education

23:26.613 --> 23:31.493
is just as important as math or science.

23:33.203 --> 23:34.162
Yeah?

23:35.205 --> 23:36.039
Yeah.

23:38.166 --> 23:39.042
What's your name?

23:39.626 --> 23:40.460
Mark.

23:41.628 --> 23:43.338
It improves critical thinking,

23:43.588 --> 23:45.090
encourages innovation,

23:45.173 --> 23:48.135
and strengthens your connection
with community.

23:50.262 --> 23:51.221
I'm Nicole.

23:54.141 --> 23:54.975
I know.

24:00.772 --> 24:01.940
So, let's call your dad.

24:02.023 --> 24:03.942
-[Nicole chuckles]
-That'd be fun.

24:04.568 --> 24:05.944
<i>-That'd be fun...</i>
-[Nicole chuckles]

24:10.615 --> 24:11.867
[Nicole coughing]

24:13.493 --> 24:14.953
[continues coughing]

24:18.331 --> 24:19.583
[gasping]

24:19.666 --> 24:20.792
[coughs]

24:22.961 --> 24:23.795
[groans]

24:25.046 --> 24:25.881
[groans]

24:26.715 --> 24:28.133
[coughs]

24:28.967 --> 24:30.427
[gasping]

24:31.470 --> 24:32.512
[exhales]

24:36.057 --> 24:37.350
[coughs]

24:38.101 --> 24:38.977
[groans]

24:39.728 --> 24:40.645
[grunts]

24:44.483 --> 24:45.317
[grunts]

24:45.734 --> 24:47.611
[grunting]

24:49.362 --> 24:51.114
[panting]

24:52.240 --> 24:53.408
[coughing]

24:54.618 --> 24:55.577
Dion!

24:57.871 --> 24:59.581
[children chattering indistinctly]

25:04.461 --> 25:07.964
Jonathan, you have to present this stuff
in a couple of minutes!

25:08.048 --> 25:09.674
You said I wouldn't have to talk.

25:09.758 --> 25:11.843
That was before Dion bailed.

25:12.969 --> 25:15.263
Why is that can of liquid nitrogen
so small?

25:15.347 --> 25:19.392
It's the biggest one I could get online
without a driver's license, okay?

25:19.476 --> 25:21.811
-I'm here, I'm here.
-I don't have to talk?

25:21.895 --> 25:25.524
I'm sorry for bailing on you
and for being jealous of you and Jonathan.

25:25.607 --> 25:26.983
Wait, what?

25:27.150 --> 25:29.486
And for trying to fix you
when you aren't broken.

25:29.569 --> 25:31.363
You're the best friend
anybody could ask for.

25:31.905 --> 25:34.199
So please, please,
let me back into the group,

25:34.282 --> 25:36.785
and I won't let you down again, I promise.

25:45.961 --> 25:47.295
You're making it weird.

25:47.379 --> 25:48.672
I know.

25:50.215 --> 25:51.591
You gonna remember your speech?

25:52.759 --> 25:54.261
Are you gonna remember yours?

25:54.803 --> 25:56.471
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

25:56.555 --> 26:00.183
Okay, guys, let's get out there
and do some great work.

26:00.642 --> 26:03.311
[all] Go, Storm Killer!

26:03.395 --> 26:04.479
[tires squeal]

26:11.987 --> 26:13.780
[woman] <i>BIONA Technologies,</i>
<i>how can I help you?</i>

26:13.863 --> 26:17.242
-I need to speak to Suzanne Wu, please.
-[woman] <i>One moment, please.</i>

26:19.286 --> 26:21.329
-[Suzanne] <i>Hello.</i>
-It's Pat. Pat Rollins.

26:21.413 --> 26:24.374
-Nicole, is that you?
-He-- He's the storm! Pat is the storm!

26:24.457 --> 26:27.669
-Wait. What? What are you talking about?
-[Nicole] <i>Pat Rollins.</i>

26:27.752 --> 26:30.005
<i>He turned into a cyclone</i>
<i>right in front of me,</i>

26:30.088 --> 26:31.881
<i>and he's trying to kill Dion!</i>

26:32.382 --> 26:34.551
If he wanted to kill Dion,
he would have done it by now.

26:34.634 --> 26:38.471
<i>No, listen. He needs Dion to heal him,</i>
<i>like he healed the fox.</i>

26:38.555 --> 26:40.056
And killing him won't do that.

26:42.100 --> 26:43.852
He needs Dion to want to heal him.

26:43.935 --> 26:46.313
[stammers] And I need you
to get to Dion's school

26:46.396 --> 26:48.273
and stop Pat from getting to him.

26:48.356 --> 26:51.151
Uh, okay, but how do you--

26:51.234 --> 26:53.194
All the stuff that you do at BIONA,

26:53.278 --> 26:56.072
I need you to throw it at him
and save my son. Do you hear me?

26:56.573 --> 26:57.699
Yeah, yeah, I will.

26:58.700 --> 26:59.534
I will.

27:01.244 --> 27:02.078
[hangs up receiver]

27:02.162 --> 27:03.830
[thunder rumbles]

27:07.751 --> 27:09.878
-[thunder rumbles]
-[wind howls]

27:19.471 --> 27:20.930
[inhales sharply]

27:24.476 --> 27:26.019
[coughs]

27:28.229 --> 27:29.856
Is the science fair this way? Thank you.

27:29.939 --> 27:30.857
[inhales sharply]

27:31.316 --> 27:32.150
Hello.

27:33.109 --> 27:35.695
[woman over PA] <i>Team Weather Control</i>
<i>from Mr. Fry's class,</i>

27:35.779 --> 27:37.280
<i>please report to the stage.</i>

27:37.364 --> 27:39.074
[children chattering indistinctly]

27:51.753 --> 27:53.254
-[Pat] Hey.
-Pat!

27:53.338 --> 27:54.464
Hey, buddy.

27:55.840 --> 27:56.716
[Pat exhales]

27:56.800 --> 27:59.886
Uh, can I use your phone?
I got into a fight with my mom.

28:00.178 --> 28:01.012
Uh...

28:01.262 --> 28:03.139
I know. She, uh... she told me.

28:03.473 --> 28:04.557
Is she mad?

28:04.766 --> 28:08.436
No. No, no, no. She just, um...
she just wants to know you're okay.

28:09.020 --> 28:12.607
She told me to take you home,
and, uh, she'll meet us there, all right?

28:13.066 --> 28:14.859
I have to do my project first.

28:16.111 --> 28:17.779
Well, she was pretty worried. I think...

28:17.862 --> 28:20.281
I think, actually, we should probably
just go now, you know?

28:20.365 --> 28:22.534
This is gonna get us all
into the gifted program.

28:22.617 --> 28:25.036
Even Jonathan. I can't let him down.

28:25.120 --> 28:26.287
[nervous chuckle] Um...

28:26.955 --> 28:27.789
Well...

28:28.248 --> 28:29.833
[groans] Your mom was, uh, pretty--

28:29.916 --> 28:32.669
No! I made a promise. I'm not leaving.

28:32.752 --> 28:34.337
Okay. [inhales]

28:34.421 --> 28:35.880
Um... [exhales]

28:36.381 --> 28:37.215
[sniffs]

28:38.007 --> 28:39.217
But, um...

28:40.510 --> 28:43.805
[stammers] I do have to talk to you
about something. It's really important.

28:43.888 --> 28:46.766
Can you just... [inhales]
come with me for one second?

28:46.850 --> 28:48.560
It'll take a minute
and you'll be right back.

28:49.394 --> 28:50.228
Okay.

28:50.603 --> 28:51.563
I'll be right back.

28:52.772 --> 28:53.606
[Pat grunts]

29:00.905 --> 29:01.740
Hey.

29:02.824 --> 29:04.242
Hey, wait, wait, wait, wait.

29:04.784 --> 29:05.660
[Pat exhales]

29:06.661 --> 29:08.663
Okay, listen.

29:09.414 --> 29:10.331
So...

29:10.415 --> 29:11.249
[sniffs]

29:11.332 --> 29:13.501
I need you to do something for me.

29:13.585 --> 29:15.253
-Okay.
-Okay.

29:15.920 --> 29:18.339
I need you to heal me...

29:19.090 --> 29:20.633
like you healed that fox.

29:20.717 --> 29:22.343
But won't that make me sick?

29:22.844 --> 29:23.970
Uh, it--

29:25.013 --> 29:26.681
It might. It might, but...

29:27.599 --> 29:30.810
but we know how
to make you better now, right? [coughs]

29:31.853 --> 29:34.230
So, is it your head again, or...?

29:34.314 --> 29:35.398
[sighs] Uh...

29:36.483 --> 29:38.693
[sniffs] Here's the thing, buddy. Um...

29:38.777 --> 29:41.529
I... I am sicker than I told you.

29:41.613 --> 29:42.447
Um...

29:43.698 --> 29:45.200
I... [sighs]

29:45.992 --> 29:47.076
-I'm dying.
-No!

29:47.160 --> 29:50.538
Dion, no, but you can save me.

29:52.373 --> 29:53.792
So, will you do that for me?

29:54.751 --> 29:55.585
Please.

29:59.255 --> 30:00.757
Can I ask my mom?

30:01.466 --> 30:03.009
[exhales shakily] Uh...

30:03.092 --> 30:03.927
[inhales]

30:04.010 --> 30:06.137
No, um, she's...

30:06.221 --> 30:07.055
[exhales]

30:07.347 --> 30:09.474
She's not here,
and I don't have a lot of time, Di,

30:09.557 --> 30:11.184
so I need you to do it right now.

30:12.560 --> 30:14.521
You're a superhero, right?

30:15.104 --> 30:16.606
Superheroes save people.

30:17.690 --> 30:21.694
So now is your chance
to be a real-life superhero.

30:25.198 --> 30:26.241
Please, Dion.

30:26.866 --> 30:27.951
You're my only hope.

30:33.039 --> 30:33.873
[Pat exhales]

30:35.708 --> 30:36.668
[Dion grunts]

30:39.546 --> 30:41.256
[children chattering indistinctly]

30:44.592 --> 30:45.426
Dion?

30:48.012 --> 30:48.847
Dion?

30:51.349 --> 30:52.517
Hey, Esperanza.

30:52.934 --> 30:54.394
Do you know where Dion is?

30:54.811 --> 30:56.688
He went down there with his mentor.

30:58.356 --> 30:59.315
Oh, my God.

30:59.899 --> 31:01.442
We've gotta get down there.

31:01.734 --> 31:03.027
-Let's go.
-Okay.

31:04.445 --> 31:05.530
-[Dion grunts]
-Dion!

31:05.613 --> 31:07.073
-Stop!
-I'm helping Pat.

31:07.156 --> 31:08.241
No!

31:08.616 --> 31:09.617
No, stop it!

31:10.159 --> 31:12.370
-Keep going, Dion.
-He's gonna die.

31:12.453 --> 31:14.205
-No, he's killing you!
-He's my friend!

31:14.289 --> 31:15.915
He is the Crooked Man!

31:17.208 --> 31:19.836
He killed your father.
He just tried to kill me.

31:19.919 --> 31:22.422
You're just mad
because he tried to kiss you!

31:22.505 --> 31:23.339
No.

31:24.048 --> 31:26.009
Hey, it's you and me.

31:27.594 --> 31:29.804
You and me, okay? You gotta trust me.

31:30.555 --> 31:31.890
[Pat groans]

31:34.642 --> 31:35.977
[Pat grunting]

31:36.394 --> 31:38.104
[Nicole yelps] No!

31:38.521 --> 31:39.564
No!

31:39.647 --> 31:43.151
-Dion, run!
-Hey! Dion, finish what you started.

31:43.234 --> 31:45.236
What are you doing? Let go of her!

31:45.320 --> 31:48.072
You've gotta finish healing me
or I'm gonna hurt your mom, okay?

31:48.156 --> 31:49.532
Dion, run!

31:49.616 --> 31:52.535
Finish healing me,
or I'm gonna have to kill her.

31:52.619 --> 31:53.453
[grunts]

31:53.536 --> 31:56.331
-Dion! Do it now.
-[Nicole] No!

31:58.124 --> 32:00.126
-[Nicole coughs]
-He's sick, Mom.

32:00.209 --> 32:01.085
I can help him.

32:01.169 --> 32:02.295
-[groans] Oh!
-[Dion] Stop!

32:02.378 --> 32:04.297
If I heal him, he won't be evil anymore.

32:04.714 --> 32:06.966
-That's my buddy.
-Please, Dion. Don't!

32:07.675 --> 32:08.968
[Nicole, distressed] Stop!

32:09.427 --> 32:11.512
[Nicole whimpering]

32:13.681 --> 32:15.266
-[Pat] Ah! Ah!
-[Nicole] Run!

32:15.350 --> 32:16.643
Run, run, run, run!

32:16.976 --> 32:17.810
Go!

32:18.811 --> 32:20.647
[grunting]

32:21.648 --> 32:23.900
[electricity crackles]

32:23.983 --> 32:25.526
Where's the door? I don't see the door.

32:25.610 --> 32:27.320
-It's right down there.
-[thunder rumbles]

32:27.403 --> 32:28.947
-[Esperanza] There they are.
-Esperanza!

32:29.030 --> 32:30.281
Go! Go, go!

32:30.949 --> 32:32.951
Go, go! Come on!

32:33.493 --> 32:34.327
Go!

32:47.757 --> 32:49.550
[dramatic music playing]

32:50.259 --> 32:51.970
[Dion] Go, go, go, go, go, go, go!

32:52.387 --> 32:53.888
Go! Go!

32:54.430 --> 32:55.264
It's coming!

32:59.769 --> 33:00.979
-Hurry!
-It's real.

33:01.062 --> 33:02.063
Come on, Dion.

33:02.855 --> 33:03.731
Come on, Esperanza.

33:03.815 --> 33:05.149
-Try the other one.
-Go in there.

33:07.235 --> 33:08.820
[loud rumbling]

33:08.903 --> 33:09.904
The storm!

33:10.989 --> 33:12.198
Take this, storm.

33:12.323 --> 33:13.741
[machine whirring]

33:16.661 --> 33:18.830
-[storm subsides]<i></i>
-[machine clicks off]

33:18.913 --> 33:21.165
It worked. It's gone.

33:23.918 --> 33:25.253
[screams]

33:25.545 --> 33:27.964
-Go!
-Come on. Come on, come on.

33:28.047 --> 33:29.674
-Let's go.
-In here!

33:33.678 --> 33:36.597
-Hey, stay in here.
-No, come with us!

33:37.181 --> 33:38.516
That was insane!

33:38.599 --> 33:41.519
Yeah, next time we better bring
a storm surge or something.

33:41.602 --> 33:43.229
-What are you doing?
-Making armor.

33:43.312 --> 33:45.148
Why? We're safe in here, right?

33:45.231 --> 33:46.524
-[Dion] He wants me.
-Why?

33:46.607 --> 33:48.651
I'm going out there
before he hurts my mom.

33:48.735 --> 33:50.486
-Dion, are you nuts?
-[Esperanza] No, Dion!

33:50.570 --> 33:54.073
-Stay in here until it goes away.
-It won't go away. I have to face it.

33:54.157 --> 33:56.951
-[Esperanza] But--
-Esperanza, he killed my dad.

33:58.453 --> 34:00.788
[thunder rumbles]

34:02.707 --> 34:04.417
-What's happening?
-[thunder rumbles]

34:04.500 --> 34:05.585
Come on. Let's go, let's go!

34:06.294 --> 34:09.005
-[Suzanne] Get the compressor!
-Hey! What's the plan?

34:09.088 --> 34:11.716
We're gonna boost liquid nitrogen
up and over the center of the storm

34:11.799 --> 34:13.176
and cool it down, try to weaken it.

34:13.259 --> 34:15.636
-That's Dion's science project.
-We thought of it first.

34:16.012 --> 34:19.015
-I'll be right back. You two stay safe.
-[Jonathan] No, wait!

34:21.726 --> 34:22.810
[screaming]

34:27.315 --> 34:28.608
No!

34:28.691 --> 34:29.609
[screams]

34:30.735 --> 34:32.070
Dion, wait!

34:34.280 --> 34:35.364
No!

34:35.698 --> 34:37.033
-Are you okay?
-[groans]

34:44.165 --> 34:46.042
-Come on!
-[Nicole] I gotta help Dion.

34:46.125 --> 34:47.335
[yells]

34:47.710 --> 34:48.586
[grunting]

34:50.296 --> 34:51.756
[Dion yelling]

34:53.341 --> 34:54.926
-What do you need?
-[Nicole] Metal.

34:55.009 --> 34:56.803
Something that could make a lightning rod.

34:57.261 --> 34:58.096
[Dion grunting]

35:01.057 --> 35:02.308
[Dion grunting]

35:05.603 --> 35:07.647
I need to get as close as I can
to that thing.

35:07.730 --> 35:10.066
He can't see you. He never reacted to you.

35:10.149 --> 35:11.984
-He knocked me out.
-By accident.

35:12.527 --> 35:14.987
I know what it looks like
when people don't see you.

35:21.536 --> 35:22.912
[yells]

35:23.287 --> 35:24.455
[grunting]

35:25.706 --> 35:26.541
[groans]

35:27.834 --> 35:29.418
[yells]

35:29.502 --> 35:32.839
He sees Dion,
but for whatever reason, you're invisible.

35:33.422 --> 35:36.008
It's because I don't have powers.
He can only see powered people.

35:36.425 --> 35:37.260
Will this work?

35:40.763 --> 35:41.597
Ah!

35:42.140 --> 35:42.974
[grunts]

35:43.474 --> 35:44.308
[groans]

35:49.272 --> 35:51.190
[shrieks]

35:53.192 --> 35:55.194
[crackling]

35:57.405 --> 35:58.906
[Mark groans]

36:01.617 --> 36:02.618
Dad?

36:13.379 --> 36:15.256
[Nicole panting]

36:23.222 --> 36:24.182
No!

36:24.265 --> 36:25.224
[yells]

36:27.852 --> 36:28.936
Aim here!

36:29.020 --> 36:29.854
[grunts]

36:29.937 --> 36:32.732
[yells]

36:32.815 --> 36:35.610
[roaring]

36:35.693 --> 36:36.527
[yells]

36:36.903 --> 36:38.404
[whimpers]

36:38.654 --> 36:40.031
Get down!

36:41.199 --> 36:42.992
[electricity pulsating]

36:43.075 --> 36:44.577
[shrieking]

36:48.206 --> 36:49.498
[Nicole yelps softly]

36:49.582 --> 36:52.627
[voices whispering indistinctly]

36:56.088 --> 36:58.257
[voices wailing]

37:11.938 --> 37:12.772
[grunts]

37:22.281 --> 37:23.115
Dad?

37:24.742 --> 37:25.576
Dad!

37:26.244 --> 37:27.495
Did you see what I did?

37:27.954 --> 37:29.038
Yeah, I saw you, Bug.

37:30.248 --> 37:32.041
I was all... [grunts]

37:32.124 --> 37:35.002
And he was all... [screams softly]

37:35.628 --> 37:37.546
I saw it all, man. You were great.

37:38.297 --> 37:39.131
[sniffs]

37:39.507 --> 37:40.549
You were great.

37:41.175 --> 37:42.635
Hey, hey, Dad.

37:42.718 --> 37:44.512
-I have a hermit crab named Pinchy.
-[laughing]

37:44.595 --> 37:46.764
-And a friend named Esperanza.
-Esperanza?

37:46.847 --> 37:49.100
That's great
that you're making friends. Um...

37:49.517 --> 37:50.685
Uh, listen to me, Bug.

37:50.768 --> 37:53.521
Uh, I want you
to remember something for me,

37:53.604 --> 37:56.190
and you can't forget it
because it's very important.

37:56.482 --> 37:57.900
Energy never dies.

37:58.818 --> 37:59.652
Okay? It just...

38:00.444 --> 38:02.029
It just takes a different form.

38:02.697 --> 38:04.573
So, whatever that thing was,

38:05.658 --> 38:06.826
it's still out there.

38:07.660 --> 38:09.078
So I need you to be careful,

38:09.787 --> 38:11.998
and I need you to be strong.

38:13.249 --> 38:15.167
The world is gonna need you one day.

38:16.252 --> 38:18.629
But if evil isn't gone,
neither is good, right?

38:18.963 --> 38:20.548
You're still out there, too.

38:22.341 --> 38:23.384
Such a smart kid.

38:24.844 --> 38:26.762
I'm gonna find a way
to bring you back.

38:27.972 --> 38:28.806
Okay.

38:29.890 --> 38:30.766
Okay.

38:40.943 --> 38:41.777
[Mark] Mmm.

38:45.239 --> 38:46.657
I'm so sorry...

38:47.325 --> 38:48.909
I didn't tell you everything.

38:50.411 --> 38:51.329
It's okay.

38:53.831 --> 38:54.665
No, it's not.

38:56.459 --> 39:00.379
No, it is definitely not okay.

39:09.930 --> 39:10.765
[Mark] Mmm.

39:17.938 --> 39:18.814
I love you.

39:21.192 --> 39:22.068
I love you.

39:51.138 --> 39:53.599
[Jonathan]
Dude, that was amazing. Are you okay?

39:53.933 --> 39:55.226
That was scary.

39:55.768 --> 39:57.269
[indistinct chattering]

39:59.188 --> 40:00.356
[Esperanza] Hey, Dion!

40:01.107 --> 40:02.900
-Over here, Dion!
-Esperanza!

40:06.112 --> 40:08.114
[Nicole] <i>I always knew you were special.</i>

40:10.116 --> 40:13.619
<i>But we're way past special now.</i>

40:17.248 --> 40:19.500
<i>I wish I could keep you safe forever.</i>

40:22.837 --> 40:23.671
<i>But...</i>

40:24.922 --> 40:26.966
<i>that's not how this works.</i>

40:28.050 --> 40:29.176
[Dion snoring lightly]

40:37.893 --> 40:39.562
<i>I don't know what's coming.</i>

40:42.064 --> 40:44.191
<i>But I can promise you one thing.</i>

40:48.028 --> 40:49.071
[exhales]

40:49.155 --> 40:50.489
<i>Whatever it is...</i>

40:53.367 --> 40:54.910
<i>will have to go through me...</i>

40:56.120 --> 40:56.954
<i>first.</i>

41:03.294 --> 41:04.545
[birds chirping]

41:11.719 --> 41:13.095
["The Old Rugged Cross" plays]

41:13.471 --> 41:14.513
[chickens clucking]

